  "text": "The Kubernetes API server audit logging system is implemented across multiple coordinated components:\n\n## Audit Event Creation from Requests\nThe `WithAudit` handler in `pkg/endpoints/filters/audit.go` is the main entry point that intercepts HTTP requests and creates audit events. It works in conjunction with `WithAuditInit` in `pkg/endpoints/filters/audit_init.go` which initializes the audit context and generates/manages audit IDs. The audit context is stored using `WithAuditContext` in `pkg/audit/context.go` and propagated throughout the request lifecycle. Request metadata is logged via `LogRequestMetadata` in `pkg/audit/request.go`, which captures user info, source IPs, resource references, and request URIs. Request and response objects are logged separately through `LogRequestObject` and `LogResponseObject` functions that can omit managed fields if configured.\n\n## Audit Policy Evaluation  \nThe `PolicyRuleEvaluator` interface defined in `pkg/audit/evaluator.go` is implemented by `policyRuleEvaluator` in `pkg/audit/policy/checker.go`. The `EvaluatePolicyRule` method matches incoming requests against configured audit policy rules using the `ruleMatches` function which evaluates users, user groups, verbs, namespaces, resources, and non-resource URLs. Policy configuration is loaded from files via `pkg/audit/policy/reader.go` and validated by `pkg/apis/audit/validation/validation.go`. The evaluated policy determines the audit level (None, Metadata, Request, RequestResponse) and which stages to omit.\n\n## Audit Backend Dispatch\nAudit events are dispatched to backends through a composable architecture. The `Backend` interface in `pkg/audit/types.go` defines the contract for audit backends with `ProcessEvents`, `Run`, and `Shutdown` methods. The `Union` function in `pkg/audit/union.go` allows multiple backends to be composed together. The three main backend implementations are:\n- Log backend (`plugin/pkg/audit/log/backend.go`): Writes events to files in legacy or JSON format\n- Webhook backend (`plugin/pkg/audit/webhook/webhook.go`): Sends events to external HTTP endpoints with exponential backoff retry\n- Buffered backend (`plugin/pkg/audit/buffered/buffered.go`): Batches events and optionally throttles sending to delegate backends\n\nBackend initialization and options are configured in `pkg/server/options/audit.go` which coordinates the selection and composition of backends.\n\n## Audit Truncation for Large Bodies\nThe truncate backend (`plugin/pkg/audit/truncate/truncate.go`) wraps a delegate backend and removes request/response objects when events exceed `MaxEventSize`, while keeping metadata intact. It calculates event sizes by serializing them and adds an annotation to indicate truncation occurred. Events in a batch are split if they exceed `MaxBatchSize` before being sent to the delegate backend.\n\n## Supporting Infrastructure\nThe audit system uses a scheme and codec factory defined in `pkg/audit/scheme.go` for serializing audit events in both v1 and internal API versions. Event formatting for text output is handled by `pkg/audit/format.go`. Metrics tracking audit events and errors are defined in `pkg/audit/metrics.go`. Audit event types are defined in `pkg/apis/audit/types.go` and `pkg/apis/audit/v1/types.go`. The admission audit hook in `pkg/admission/audit.go` allows request handlers to log audit annotations during request processing."
